                        "content": "The nurse would question the physician if which medication were prescribed for a client with glaucoma?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPilocarpine and carbachol are examples of miotic agents used in the treatment of glaucoma. Atropine sulfate is a mydriatic and cycloplegic medication that is contraindicated for use in clients with glaucoma. Mydriatic medications dilate the pupil and can cause an increase in intraocular pressure in the eye.",
                        "id": "455e4516fdc24bda9383a6efd8bc9df8",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
