                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse working in a long-term care facility notes that several clients are taking pilocarpine hydrochloride eye drops. The nurse ensures that which medication is available on the nursing unit for use if a client should develop systemic toxicity from pilocarpine hydrochloride?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPilocarpine hydrochloride is a cholinergic agent. Atropine sulfate must be available in the event of systemic toxicity from pilocarpine hydrochloride. Pilocarpine toxicity is manifested by vertigo, bradycardia, tremors, hypotension, syncope, cardiac dysrhythmias, and seizures. Disulfiram is an alcohol deterrent used in the management of alcoholism in selected clients. Cyclopentolate is a rapidly acting mydriatic and cycloplegic medication used preoperatively for surgical procedures on the eye. Naloxone hydrochloride is an opioid antagonist used to reverse opioid-induced respiratory depression.",
                        "id": "a12d4ab85239425e87e1e841e8dc5281",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "4fe72aa650f4423da8c817ebe5c3eb08",
                                "content": "Clarify the prescription for the atropine sulfate."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "09460b4625774198a46e9bd8587a0c07",
                                "content": "Clarify the prescription for the pilocarpine hydrochloride."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "654b3f51b703419da513e4dab86d3022",
                                "content": "Determine the date of the scheduled follow-up PHCP visit."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "ec0a0899b2f042a28db40b611b89fbfc",
                                "content": "Determine the extent of the intraocular pressure caused by the glaucoma."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "4fe72aa650f4423da8c817ebe5c3eb08",
                                    "content": "Clarify the prescription for the atropine sulfate."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "09460b4625774198a46e9bd8587a0c07",
                                    "content": "Clarify the prescription for the pilocarpine hydrochloride."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "654b3f51b703419da513e4dab86d3022",
                                    "content": "Determine the date of the scheduled follow-up PHCP visit."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "ec0a0899b2f042a28db40b611b89fbfc",
                                    "content": "Determine the extent of the intraocular pressure caused by the glaucoma."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        "isSubmit": "0",
                        "delFlag": "0",
                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The home care nurse is reviewing the record of a client newly diagnosed with glaucoma who is scheduled for a home visit. The nurse notes that the primary health care provider (PHCP) has prescribed atropine sulfate and pilocarpine hydrochloride eye drops. The nurse would contact the PHCP before the home visit for which reason?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAtropine sulfate is a mydriatic and cycloplegic medication that is contraindicated in clients with glaucoma. Mydriatic medications dilate the pupil and cause increased intraocular pressure in the eye. Pilocarpine hydrochloride is a miotic agent used in the treatment of glaucoma. It is unnecessary to contact the PHCP regarding the date for follow-up treatment. In fact, the client may know this date, which the nurse can ask about during the home care visit. It is unnecessary to know the extent of the intraocular pressure caused by the glaucoma in planning care for the client.",
                        "id": "c8da183cd2b64eddb4b3405131a12373",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "969a3b9a86d542dca93ff38dc852021b",
                                "content": "The medication dilates the pupil of the operative eye."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "4f37c37b01c141fc9d4c6dd9f771320a",
                                "content": "The medication constricts the pupil of the operative eye."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
